		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Metarie, LA 8/24/02 HooHA! ugh....WHEE!<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=7058'>Jonathan "Carny" brown</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=7058&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 26, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> okay, well, it&#39;s time for another TR from me...me! I guess this one starts with a little pre-tourney, where I have been running through about 5-7 decks to play. Last week, I played Trust with Nazgul, similar to Beedo&#39;s Deck, running Horn and some other personal cards that I like to use. It did well, but I had low SoS somehow and didn&#39;t even get to play my bud Rob, who has been dominating lately. He actually ended up losing in the Finals, which he often does, which is why he hates them. Anyways, I tried out a Hobbit deck, with 4 PATHS and Bilbo/Proudfoot to get 4 PATHS at 9, but it actually seemed to lose to Moria Archery, which is popular with a couple of guys I don&#39;t intend to lose to. So, I checked out Hayes deck, and it&#39;s tight, but I little shallow for my taste, so I up it to 64 cardsm switch out a few things, such as adding in 4 PATHS, dropping one of the 2 Sleeps, etc. I also change up the Uruk side to a more twilight efficient, since Denial seems to be popular. So, I test it with my girlfriend Noelle, and it loses to a bad draw, but then dominates after that. I am satisfied, and heres what I ended up with<br />
<br />
Start<br />
<br />
Frodo, RA<br />
The Bane<br />
Arwen, DoE<br />
Legolas, G<br />
<br />
Companions<br />
<br />
Aragorn, HttWC x 4<br />
Boromir, LoG x 2<br />
Gandalf, FotS x 2<br />
Sam, SoH<br />
<br />
Allies<br />
<br />
Thrarin<br />
Filbert<br />
<br />
Events<br />
<br />
PATHS x 4<br />
Pathfinder<br />
Sleep, Caradhras<br />
<br />
Conditions<br />
<br />
O Elbereth!<br />
No Stranger x 3<br />
<br />
Possessions<br />
<br />
Ranger&#39;s Sword<br />
Aragorn&#39;s Bow<br />
Flaming Brand x 2<br />
Armor x 2<br />
Gwemegil<br />
Sting<br />
Athelas<br />
<br />
Minions<br />
<br />
Saruman, KoI x 3<br />
Uruk Ravager x 2<br />
Uruk Lieutanant x 3<br />
Uruk Warrior x 4<br />
Uruk Captain x 2<br />
Troop of Uruk-Hai x 4<br />
Lurtz, SoI x 2<br />
The Balrog, DB<br />
<br />
Events<br />
<br />
