8 Gates of Argonath<br />
9 Slopes of Amon Hen (this site RULES)<br />
<br />
So, thats it. Here come da PAIN!<br />
<br />
Game 1 Freddy<br />
<br />
Trust/Horn w/ Nazgul and Gandalf Hate.<br />
<br />
Freddy is playing a larger version of the deck I played last week, with more allies, aka a greater focus on the Horn and more companions. It&#39;s a good deck, but he doesn&#39;t get the cards he needs when he needs them. So, we start off with me bidding I think 3 and him bidding 0, so I go first with the Dragon, don&#39;t draw Aragorn( a trend that would continue ) pull Sam and move to the Bree Streets. He plays a guy, who I shoot with Lego twice and then PATHS away. I stop. He plays Gandalf, Sam from deck and moves and I manage a Troop and some conditions. He stops. I movfe to the Ford after playing Aragorn, Sword and Brand(he he) and Legolas is promptly Charged. D&#39;oh! But Legolas doesn&#39;t matter, so I kill the guy he plays and draw up Gwemegil. I stop. He moves to the Ford and I play one guy and No Bussiness, he stops. I drop No Stranger, Gwemegil and move, he gets 4 Twilight and Gates in someone, who I kill. I move again and survive the Witch King that shows, but Arwen gets breathed. He moves to 4, I play Saruman and he stops. I move to 6, after dropping another No Stranger and Boromir. He plays someone, who also dies. I stop. He moves to 5, but is stopped by Lurtz and a Troop. I Move from 6-8, because I can, and draw into O Elbereth AND Filbert, so that seals the game. He moves to 6, but stops cause it doesn&#39;t matter. I move to 9 and face the Witch King, Narya, Elrond and I think Aragorn&#39;s Bow, who are no trouble for Boromir, Gandalf, Arwen and Aragorn. <br />
<br />
FW +3 (3)<br />
<br />
highs: trouncing nazgul, who are SO in fasion lately.<br />
lows: not killing anyone on consequence, although I did get to double Savagery Lurtz...he he.<br />
<br />
Game 2 Noelle (my DARLING)<br />
Gandalf, tgP Start, much like the Brahma Bull&#39;s deck. Gandalf hating shadow side.<br />
<br />
well, we played this matchup at home several times and it came down to whether or not I drew Gwemegil or Flaming Brands early. This game, I drew up Aragorn and both Brand before site 4. I double every time after site 3, from 3-5, 5-7, 7-9. The great thing was that she was PIMPING the Uruks, even though I drew up Saruman and Pumps quite regularly. I was quite happy with the way her deck ran, and had she bid higher, I REALLY think that she would have made it to nine first. <br />
FW +3 (6)<br />
<br />
highs: 2 brands at the ford?<br />
lows: beating the love of my life.<br />
<br />
Game 3 Rob<br />
Gandalf, FotS start, versatile fellowship/ Uruks.<br />
<br />
well, Rob has recently surpassed me as first in LA, because it seems that every time I play him, I get the worst draw possible. Besides that, he is a very good player, and his deck doesn&#39;t have all that many weaknesses. So, I bid 3 and he bids 0, as I knew he would, and I go first. I do NOT get Aragorn, but I draw Boromir and Armor. So I play those, get Sam and move into a Troop, which eats Sam, get Savagery&#39;d and hit Boromir for 1. I stop. He plays Aragorn, HttWC, and moves into a Troop. Sound familiar? He moves again, which I don&#39;t blame him for, and I play a little guy and get out No Bussiness and somethine else. I get Aragorn and 2 No Strangers, move and face little and stop. He moves to Hollin into Saruman and another No Bussiness, which means he can&#39;t Dreary me out of both of them, since he already pitched a Saruman&#39;s Ambition. He stops. I play some weapons, but leave the Council Courtyard with ZERO in the pool. I give him 5 twilight, just for my people, and he gets out a Troop. I hit it twice with archery and let Legolas take 2. I move again and he plays only Lurtz. I play three PATHS to kill Lurtz and Legolas gets eaten by the Troop. He moves to the bridge and I play lobe Saruman again, and there is a PISS load of Twilight, cause he play a bunch of companions. I have in my hand 3 Savageries and no Minions, but he stops, so pitch a Savagery and draw into Lieutenant. Lurtz and Troop. Good thing he stopped! I move from 5-6, facing nothing and stop. He moves to 6, facing little, and moves again, but this time I am able to muster Lurtz, Troop Lietenant and i think a Warrior. He gets beat up pretty bad, due to 2 Savageries, but survives, after losing down to 4 companions. I move to 7 and he plays Saruman&#39;s Power to ditch my No Strangers, but I kill the guy he plays and move again, so he has to double if he wants to win. He plays again something that I can handle. He moves to 8 and I play Saruman, and even though I have 4 Uruks in hand, I hold them. He knows he can&#39;t touch my fellowship, so he goes again. I get out 5 Uruks against Sam, PP, Aragorn, HttWC(exhausted), Gandalf, FotS(exhausted) and Frodo, RA with no weapons. Since I play the Slopes, I get to play 2 Troop, Warrior and Lieutanant and a Captain, along with Saruman, who was already in play. He concedes, because 1 Uruk would kill Frodo, and at least one was getting on him no matter what.<br />
<br />
FW +3 (9)<br />
<br />
highs: beating rob...geez, finnaly<br />
lows: Saruman alone...but you hafta move....nasty.<br />
<br />
Game 4 Stephen<br />
Aragorn, HttWC start Denial/ Sauron UTWE/Bowmen deck.<br />
<br />
I bid 3, he bids 4 and he goes first, I think. anyways, we are both playing the Green Dragon, so I pull Sam and actually get Aragorn in the hand, so I play him, but not Boromir, because I know he plays Enquea, and I move. I feed Sam to someone and move again. I have to shoot someone with Legolas, but it&#39;s not a problem. He moves to 2, but has to stop for some reason I can&#39;t remember. I move to the Eregion Hills, so now I have to watch out for Evil. He plays a little guy or two, but I kill and move again. He plays his Enquea, and I kill it with Aragorn, so now I know it&#39;s safe, plus I got rid of Legolas. He moves to 3 after playing Arwen, ER and a No Stranger, I have enough for someone that he can fight and kill, but he stops. I move to 6 safely, after playing Sleep to get rid of 3 Bowmen and 2 UTWE. YEAH! He moves to 4 and I play Saruman. He moves again and I get out 4 guys, 2 Warriors and 2 Troops. He puts one on each guy, inlcuding Warrior on Frodo with Sting and Elbereth. I have out 2 Ambitions and a Savagery, he resolves Frodo and I pay all three pumps, which overhwelms Frodo. The ring goes to Sam, which makes him a 5, so Sam survives the first fight. Arwen and Aragorn both take 2 and then die on the fierce, and Sam takes 1 and 2 burdens with the rare ring. I move to 7 and face a few little guys, but stop. He moves to 6 and I get out something small, but he lives. I move to 8, which is the Anduin Banks. Apparently I have 5 companions, so that and 1 Bowmen means archery, unless I shoot the ONE guy he played. Turns out he was holding guys, trying to get enough to get some one Frodo. I shoot him with Aragorn and stop. He moves to the Confluence(which I had Pathfound) and loses Filbert, so I play 2 Ravagers and he gets overwhelmed. <br />
<br />
FW +3 (12)<br />
<br />
so, I am the only 4-0, and Rob beat Noelle in round 4, so it Rob and I in the Finals. The final game was much like our other, except he didn&#39;t get Aragorn, and so he couldn&#39;t double. The game ended when dropped Aragorn, sword, Gandalf&#39;s Staff and Legolas and site 5, where I played Saruman and enough Uruks to get 2-3 on Frodo. It was not pretty. Yeh! I win. So I am happy, and we get our prize support and theres CRAP in there. I buy the next 6 packs and pull, in this order:<br />
<br />
Wealth of Moria<br />
Orc War Band<br />
Beauty is Fading<br />
Toldea (meh...)<br />
Arwen WHEEE!<br />
Goblin Armory WHEE!<br />
<br />
so, not too bad. anyways, hopefully that was enjoyable. Later. <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3940&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
